#### Visual Studio Feedback System on 4/10/2020, 00:02 AM: 

Thank you for taking the time to provide your suggestion.  We will do some preliminary checks to make sure we can proceed further.  We'll provide an update once the issue has been triaged by the product team.

Wasm currently implements these opcodes but without the overflow checks.  This PR adds the checks just for add.ovf and add.ovf.un for 32 and 64 bit ints.  I've done it starting with this idea 
```
    if (a > 0 && b > INT_MAX - a) {
        /* handle overflow */
    } else if (a < 0 && b < INT_MIN - a) {
        /* handle underflow */
    }
    return a + b;
```
from https://codereview.stackexchange.com/questions/37177/simple-method-to-detect-int-overflow.  Unsigned checks are simpler as `a<0` is always false.

If this looks ok I can create similar checks for sub and mul.  WIP as depends on exception support in https://github.com/dotnet/corert/pull/7137
